07/04/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Adriean Videanu officially assumed the post of Bucharest mayor Wednesday (6 April), after election officials certified his victory in Sunday's race. The former deputy prime minister ran on behalf of the ruling coalition and won the race with 53 per cent of the vote, defeating Marian Vanghelie of the opposition Social Democratic Party, who got 29.6 per cent. The position had been vacant since December, when Traian Basescu was elected president. (Nine o'clock - 06/04/05)
